      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification provided for all major modeling assumptions; sensitivity of QoI to model form choices quantified.",
      "rationale": "Continuum mechanics with bilinear isotropic hardening is well-established for Ti-6Al-4V under quasi-static loading. Sensitivity analyses showed QoI insensitivity (<1.5%) to kinematic versus isotropic hardening choice. Thread geometry is represented by equivalent axisymmetric cross-section, consistent with published literature for F1717 FEA. Geometric nonlinearity (large displacement) enabled; confirmed necessary by 4.2% QoI shift versus small-displacement assumption."
