      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU operating conditions; at minimum two loading configurations assessed.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single loading condition (ASTM F1717 standard compression-bending configuration, 10° offset angle). The COU is specifically defined for this loading condition, so a single test configuration is appropriate for the intended use. However, the required level of 3 demands at least two loading configurations to bound uncertainty; only one was tested, resulting in an achieved level of 2. This gap is acknowledged and accepted given the narrowly defined COU scope."
    },
