      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for all QoI; combined validation uncertainty budget documented; acceptance threshold pre-specified.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement per ASME V&V 10.1 methodology. Combined uncertainty includes experimental measurement uncertainty (load cell ±0.5%, displacement ±0.1 mm), inter-specimen variability (CV 4–7%), and simulation numerical uncertainty (mesh + solver, 0.9%). Maximum E/uval across all QoI and both laboratories: 1.71, below the pre-specified threshold of 1.96. All QoI differences <10%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
