      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI directly linked to device failure modes and regulatory decision; clinical relevance of each QoI documented.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness relates to load sharing with the spine and subsidence risk. Yield force is the primary safety-relevant QoI, as permanent deformation of the screw-rod construct indicates structural failure. Force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield energy absorption. All three QoI are explicitly required by FDA guidance for spinal fixation device submissions and are directly predictive of the failure modes assessed in the COU."
    },
